entry.et: Middle English elles, from Old English; akin to Latin alius other, alter other of two, Greek allos other

def.dt: :in a different manner or place or at a different time how else could he have acted here and nowhere else
:in an additional manner or place or at an additional time where else is gold found
:if not :otherwise leave or else you'll be sorry used absolutely to express a threat do what I tell you or else
:being different in identity it must have been somebody else
:being in addition what else did he say?

entry.pr: ˈsəm(p)-thiŋ, especially in rapid speech or for 2 ˈsəm-pᵊm

def.dt: :some indeterminate amount more than a specified number used in combination twenty-something years old a group of fifty-somethings
:one having more or less the character, qualities, or nature of something different is something of a bore
